        "content": "<p>Ah sorry for the confusion.  There's a math question and a lean question.  Here's the lean part first:</p>\n<p>The claim ğ“Ë¢ (U + V) â‰¤ ğ“Ë¢ U + ğ“Ë¢ V holds generally.  Let W be any set in ğ“Ë¢ U + ğ“Ë¢ V, and let U' and V' be open sets with U âŠ† U', V âŠ† V', and U' + V' âŠ† W.  Then U' + V' is an open set with U + V âŠ† U' + V' âŠ† W, so W is in ğ“Ë¢ (U + V).  I'm stuck translating this into lean because I don't understand the nhdsSet API well enough to pull out the U' and V' that satisfy those conditions.</p>",
